<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - Quora Lite</title>

    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            background: #f5f7fa;
        }

        /* Navbar */
        .navbar {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 15px 30px;
            background: #343a40;
            color: white;
        }

        .navbar a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin-left: 15px;
        }

        /* Content */
        .privacy {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        .privacy h1 {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .privacy h2 {
            margin-top: 20px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .privacy p {
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #555;
        }

        /* Footer */
        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 15px;
            background: #343a40;
            color: white;
            margin-top: 40px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <%- include('includes/nav.ejs') %>
    <div class="privacy">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

        <p>
            At Quora Lite, we value your privacy. This page explains how we collect, use,
            and protect your information when you use our website.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
            We may collect basic information such as your name, email, and any content
            you choose to share (like posts or messages).
        </p>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>
            Your information is used to improve the platform, allow you to create posts,
            and enhance your overall experience.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>
            We take reasonable steps to protect your data, but please note that no system
            is completely secure.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
            We do not sell your personal data. However, third-party services may be used
            for analytics or hosting.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this policy from time to time. Continued use of the site means
            you accept these changes.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
            If you have any questions, feel free to contact us through our contact page.
        </p>
    </div>

    <%- include('includes/footer.ejs') %>

</body>
</html>